    "analysis": "We narrowed metric candidates to two non-constant, non-zero-severity pairs within the incident window: os_020/Disk_io_util (strong positive deviation, high_severity=1.0) and osb_001/app.succee_rate (small low-side dip, low_severity≈0.0655). Earliest anomalies for both are at the window start (2020-05-27 00:00:00+08:00). Most other high-count anomalies were constant-series (zero severity) and are unlikely root causes. To localize the root cause component and reason we must use traces to see call relationships and whether either candidate appears as a downstream faulty element in call chains. Specifically, check trace records in the incident window for any traces emitted by or mentioning os_020 or osb_001, and collect counts, distinct trace_name values, earliest timestamps, and some sample rows to understand interactions and whether failures (e.g., high latency/error_rate) are visible in traces tied to these components.",
